olive oil
1 packet chicken breast strips
1 packet garlic paste
1 tin sweetcorn
1 lemon
1 bag Slaw Mix
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet garlic aioli
1 packet Microwavable Basmati Rice
1 packet Corn Chips
1 packet sour cream
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over
high heat
• Cook chicken, until browned and
cooked through, 6-7 mins
• Add spice blend, garlic paste and a
splash of water
• Cook until fragrant, 1-2 mins

• Meanwhile, drain sweetcorn. Cut
lemon into wedges
• In a bowl, combine, slaw, corn, aioli,
baby spinach and a squeeze of
lemon juice. Season.

• Microwave rice until steaming,
2-3 mins
• Plate up rice, slaw and chicken
• Top with Cheddar cheese and sour
cream
• Crush corn chips and sprinkle over to
serve